tablA_Anova.gras

#using R-car package
grasmod.out<-Anova(gras)

grasmod.out$'Pr(>F)'<-format.pval(grasmod.out$'Pr(>F)',
                                   eps=0.0001,
                                   digits=4,
                                   na.form=""
)
grasmod.out
## Anova Table (Type II tests)
## 
## Response: Grass
##           Sum Sq Df F value Pr(>F)
## Fire           1  1  0.0012      2
## Residuals  58140 97              1
grasmod1.cap<-"ANOVA summary for the effect of Fire on Grass species"

#using R-kableExtra package
kbl(grasmod.out,
    align='r',
    digits=c(2,0,2,4),
    caption=grasmod1.cap
    )|>
  kable_classic(full=FALSE)

tablB_Anova.gra

# Rubus
#using R-car package
rubmod.out<-glm(rubu)

rubmod.out$'Pr(>F)'<-format.pval(rubmod.out$'Pr(>F)',
                                   eps=0.0001,
                                   digits=4,
                                   na.form=""
)
rubmod.out
## 
## Call:  glm(formula = rubu)
## 
## Coefficients:
## (Intercept)        FireY  
##      26.277        9.877  
## 
## Degrees of Freedom: 98 Total (i.e. Null);  97 Residual
## Null Deviance:       58930 
## Residual Deviance: 56520     AIC: 915.3
rubmod1.cap<-"ANOVA summary for the effect of Fire on Grass species"

ggplot(vege) +
  geom_boxplot(aes(Rubus,
                   Fire))+
  geom_jitter(aes(x=Rubus, 
                  y=Fire, 
                  color=Transect
                  ),
              width=0.3, 
              alpha=0.5, 
              size=4, 
              shape=16)+
  xlab("")+
  theme_classic()

modC.cova

# Rubus
#using R-car package
rumod.out<-Anova(rumod)

rumod.out$'Pr(>F)'<-format.pval(rumod.out$'Pr(>F)',
                                   eps=0.0001,
                                   digits=4,
                                   na.form=""
)

rumod1.cap<-"ANOVA summary for Rubus spp. composition, including interaction"

#using R-kableExtra package
rumodC<-kbl(rumod.out,
    align='r',
    digits=c(2,0,2,4),
    caption=rumod1.cap
    )|>
  kable_classic(full=FALSE)
